      "content": "You can create a cast of characters that reflect the social hierarchy of the time, with the white, landowning elite at the top, followed by the poor, uneducated blacks who are just trying to survive. The activists, like those from the NAACP, can be portrayed as outsiders, always pushing for change and stirring up trouble. You can use dialogue to show the subtle (and not-so-subtle) ways that blacks are treated as second-class citizens, like being forced to sit at the back of the bus or being denied service at the local diner. For example, a black character might say, \"I'm just tryin' to get a cup of coffee, but the waitress says I gotta sit at the back counter like I'm some kinda animal.\"",
